- Create partition table on target device manually using fdisk (under Linux) or diskpart (Windows). Use exact sizing for system partitions and new, smaller size for data etc.
- Ensure target boot partition is marked as active/bootable (use fdisk or diskpart)
- Start Clonezilla EXPERT MODE
- Choose -icds option (do not check disk sizes)
- Choose -k option (do not create parition table) (ie use the one you created manually)
- Execute the clone
